1
00:00:12,280 --> 00:00:14,320
♪ You're the only one in my heart ♪

2
00:00:14,320 --> 00:00:16,000
♪ Even if you never know ♪

3
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:19,840
♪ I'll keep watching over you ♪

4
00:00:19,840 --> 00:00:23,760
♪ I love you more than words
but our path isn't easy ♪

5
00:00:23,760 --> 00:00:27,040
♪ I just need you to believe in me ♪

6
00:00:27,080 --> 00:00:30,720
♪ I'm weak for your lips ♪

7
00:00:30,720 --> 00:00:34,480
♪ And the kiss upon my forehead ♪

8
00:00:34,480 --> 00:00:41,480
♪ Every action conveys these words, you know? ♪

9
00:00:41,560 --> 00:00:44,960
♪ Can you hear me saying I love you? ♪

10
00:00:44,960 --> 00:00:47,000
♪ Use the feeling you know ♪

11
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:51,120
♪ And you'll love so deeply ♪

12
00:00:51,120 --> 00:00:55,120
♪ Can you feel my love? ♪

13
00:00:55,120 --> 00:00:59,840
♪ Please know that I love you ♪

14
00:00:59,840 --> 00:01:01,560
It's because you're like this…

15
00:01:01,560 --> 00:01:03,840
that I can never get over you.

16
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:08,720
While the divorce isn't finalized,
I can sleep with you anytime I want?

17
00:01:08,720 --> 00:01:10,600
There are plenty of ways

18
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:13,920
to make it look like we're in love.

19
00:01:13,920 --> 00:01:15,400
Then let's do all of them.

20
00:01:15,760 --> 00:01:17,800
What exactly are you making?

21
00:01:19,440 --> 00:01:20,240
Mom!

22
00:01:20,240 --> 00:01:21,640
Oh! Oh!

23
00:01:21,640 --> 00:01:23,960
-Oh!
-Stop. She's going to misunderstand.

24
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:25,040
Open the door right now!

25
00:01:25,040 --> 00:01:27,320
Give her some space, Ging.

26
00:01:27,320 --> 00:01:30,480
If I did, I'd lose to that woman.

27
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:53,680
Yes, Mom?

28
00:01:54,240 --> 00:01:55,760
I'm feeling a little dizzy.

29
00:01:55,880 --> 00:01:59,160
Can you take me to the hospital, Runch?

30
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:00,960
Of course.

31
00:02:01,480 --> 00:02:03,160
I'm on my way now.

32
00:02:23,440 --> 00:02:25,040
My mom's not feeling well.

33
00:02:25,160 --> 00:02:26,520
I need to check on her.

34
00:02:26,840 --> 00:02:28,320
I might be home late, okay?

35
00:02:28,720 --> 00:02:29,520
Hm?

36
00:02:31,720 --> 00:02:33,360
That hag is sick?

37
00:02:41,080 --> 00:02:43,000
Mom, where are you?

38
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:44,600
-She's here.
-Are you okay?

39
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:50,080
I don't think I need a doctor anymore.

40
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:51,520
I'm feeling better now.

41
00:02:54,920 --> 00:02:58,160
Anyway, do you remember Maylin?

42
00:03:01,960 --> 00:03:03,400
Maylin?

43
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:05,960
Maylinya, Samorn's daughter.

44
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:08,760
You used to play together all the time as kids.

45
00:03:10,480 --> 00:03:11,560
Oh!

46
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:14,880
Right, I remember now. Maylin.

47
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:18,240
It has been so long.

48
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:19,680
It really has.

49
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:22,640
I didn't think
we'd run into each other again so soon.

50
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:26,680
She just got back from the States two days ago.

51
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:30,720
Since you're already here,
why don't you stay for dinner?

52
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:34,400
She has so much she wants to ask you about.

53
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:36,440
You're both in law, after all.

54
00:03:36,960 --> 00:03:38,320
-Uh…
-Please?

55
00:03:38,440 --> 00:03:40,040
Pretty please?

56
00:03:41,720 --> 00:03:42,960
All right, Mom.

57
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:53,160
-Eat up, dear.
-Thank you.

58
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:57,960
Maylin starts work next week.

59
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:00,080
Why don't you give her some advice, Runch?

60
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:03,520
I'd be happy to, Maylin.

61
00:04:04,320 --> 00:04:07,680
Working in law takes a lot of attention to detail.

62
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:09,640
But more importantly,

63
00:04:09,920 --> 00:04:13,440
you have to see clients as people, not just cases.

64
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:19,720
Sometimes what they don't say
matters more than what they do.

65
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:28,560
That was really well said.

66
00:04:28,840 --> 00:04:31,240
I'm glad we met again.

67
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:34,760
Could I get your LINE ID?

68
00:04:36,160 --> 00:04:37,040
Sure.

69
00:04:38,080 --> 00:04:38,920
Here.

70
00:04:45,960 --> 00:04:46,760
Got it.

71
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:48,000
Thank you.

72
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:56,000
You should eat too, Runch.

73
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:57,040
Okay.

74
00:05:09,200 --> 00:05:10,120
Neen?

75
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:44,920
Neen.

76
00:05:45,320 --> 00:05:47,840
Open the door. I'm home.

77
00:05:48,840 --> 00:05:49,840
What is it?

78
00:05:52,360 --> 00:05:54,280
Did you bring me dinner?

79
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:03,080
Who says I bought that for you? I didn't.

80
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:06,360
But it's all my favorite food.

81
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:10,080
You waited for me, didn't you?

82
00:06:10,080 --> 00:06:13,080
No, I didn't. Why would I?

83
00:06:21,880 --> 00:06:22,760
Here.

84
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:25,960
Eat something first.

85
00:06:28,840 --> 00:06:29,760
I'm not hungry.

86
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:37,520
But your stomach…

87
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:40,440
says otherwise.

88
00:06:49,840 --> 00:06:51,160
I said I'm not hungry.

89
00:06:52,320 --> 00:06:54,960
Don't be hangry, okay?

90
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:55,960
Come on.

91
00:06:56,520 --> 00:06:58,120
Come downstairs and eat with me.

92
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:01,720
If you won't come on your own…

93
00:07:02,080 --> 00:07:03,680
I'll carry you instead.

94
00:07:04,520 --> 00:07:06,680
So? What's it going to be?

95
00:07:28,240 --> 00:07:29,920
Here.

96
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:33,840
-Your hot fried rice.
-Thanks.

97
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:37,080
-Let's eat.
-I'm digging in.

98
00:07:37,880 --> 00:07:39,360
Eat up. Try this too.

99
00:07:40,720 --> 00:07:42,160
You must be starving.

100
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:49,080
Mm.

101
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:51,920
So what was wrong with your mom?

102
00:07:52,760 --> 00:07:54,000
Her blood pressure.

103
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:55,920
Blood pressure?

104
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:58,960
She needed you to rush over for that?

105
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:03,120
At first, I was going to take her to the doctor.

106
00:08:05,560 --> 00:08:06,800
Which means…

107
00:08:07,240 --> 00:08:08,560
you didn't go?

108
00:08:09,320 --> 00:08:10,320
Why not?

109
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:14,360
She felt better, so we didn't need to.

110
00:08:14,880 --> 00:08:15,800
I knew it.

111
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:18,240
She wasn't really sick.

112
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:20,240
She just wanted an excuse to see you.

113
00:08:20,880 --> 00:08:23,160
You can never tell when she's playing you.

114
00:08:25,560 --> 00:08:27,280
She's still my mom, okay?

115
00:08:27,520 --> 00:08:29,200
Whether she was actually sick or not,

116
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:31,680
I still had to make sure she was okay.

117
00:08:33,720 --> 00:08:36,720
Right. Such a perfect daughter.

118
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:40,159
Let's eat, okay?

119
00:08:54,040 --> 00:08:55,120
Well?

120
00:08:55,720 --> 00:08:58,360
Aren't you going to check your phone?

121
00:08:58,960 --> 00:09:02,840
No, I want to focus on dinner with you.

122
00:09:03,280 --> 00:09:05,320
Nothing else matters right now.

123
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:06,880
Okay.

124
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:15,200
Okay, Mom.

125
00:09:16,480 --> 00:09:18,760
Tomorrow's my day off, so I'll go visit them.

126
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:21,280
All right.

127
00:09:21,480 --> 00:09:22,440
Bye.

128
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:26,400
Where are you going?

129
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:31,080
My mom said my grandparents miss me.

130
00:09:31,080 --> 00:09:33,680
She told me to visit them if I have time,

131
00:09:33,680 --> 00:09:35,520
so I'm going tomorrow.

132
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:39,000
Perfect. I've been missing them too.

133
00:09:39,080 --> 00:09:40,040
I'll come with you.

134
00:09:40,760 --> 00:09:41,800
Who invited you?

135
00:09:42,880 --> 00:09:44,200
I'm going alone.

136
00:09:44,840 --> 00:09:47,000
How are you supposed to go alone?

137
00:09:47,360 --> 00:09:50,880
What if your grandparents ask where I am?

138
00:09:50,880 --> 00:09:52,480
What are you going to say?

139
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:55,960
That we're getting divorced?

140
00:09:57,040 --> 00:09:59,840
They'd be shocked.

141
00:10:01,160 --> 00:10:02,280
Let's just go together, okay?

142
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:04,960
It's settled. I'm off to work.

143
00:10:04,960 --> 00:10:05,920
No, Runch…

144
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:06,880
Runch!

145
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:26,440
What are you doing?

146
00:10:29,400 --> 00:10:31,080
Packing your stuff. Obviously.

147
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:34,320
You don't have to do that.

148
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:36,640
They're my things. I can pack them myself.

149
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:40,240
I just want you to do less work.

150
00:10:44,040 --> 00:10:45,040
Thanks.

151
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:46,880
But don't do it next time.

152
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:50,120
I'll still do it anyway.

153
00:10:50,960 --> 00:10:54,800
You always forget something when you pack.

154
00:10:55,560 --> 00:10:57,880
That's not true. I can pack just fine.

155
00:11:00,480 --> 00:11:01,600
I just…

156
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:05,240
might forget sunscreen or something.

157
00:11:06,280 --> 00:11:09,440
Exactly. That's why I'm packing for you.

158
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:18,840
How nice…

159
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:21,360
What's that?

160
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:23,080
Hmm?

161
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:24,440
Nothing.

162
00:11:24,760 --> 00:11:25,800
Oh really?

163
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:28,880
Go pack your own stuff. I'm taking a shower.

164
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:32,800
What if…

165
00:11:33,280 --> 00:11:35,400
I want to shower with you?

166
00:11:36,120 --> 00:11:36,960
No.

167
00:11:37,520 --> 00:11:38,360
Just go.

168
00:11:39,880 --> 00:11:42,160
-Out.
-But I'm not done packing for you yet.

169
00:11:45,040 --> 00:11:46,960
I said I can do it myself. Go shower too.

170
00:11:47,360 --> 00:11:49,120
You sure you can handle it?

171
00:12:17,480 --> 00:12:19,680
Is this a good time, Maylin?

172
00:12:20,440 --> 00:12:23,200
I wanted to invite you out for a meal

173
00:12:23,480 --> 00:12:25,040
since it's a holiday today.

174
00:12:25,320 --> 00:12:26,960
Runch will be joining us too,

175
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:28,400
so you should come.

176
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:31,960
I'll send you the location later, okay?

177
00:12:32,600 --> 00:12:33,680
Thanks, dear.

178
00:12:34,960 --> 00:12:36,600
Who was that?

179
00:12:36,800 --> 00:12:37,640
Oh…

180
00:12:37,960 --> 00:12:40,520
that was Maylin. Samorn's daughter.

181
00:12:40,640 --> 00:12:42,600
We met her when she was little.

182
00:12:43,960 --> 00:12:45,560
Ah, I remember now.

183
00:12:45,720 --> 00:12:48,560
The cute little girl
who used to follow Runch everywhere?

184
00:12:48,560 --> 00:12:49,280
That's the one.

185
00:12:49,280 --> 00:12:50,680
Didn't she study abroad?

186
00:12:51,160 --> 00:12:54,320
She did. She just came back recently.

187
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:58,040
She even brought me gifts yesterday
right after she landed.

188
00:12:58,200 --> 00:12:59,840
Such a sweet girl.

189
00:13:00,320 --> 00:13:03,960
She's beautiful inside and out.

190
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:07,720
What a shame…

191
00:13:08,680 --> 00:13:09,960
What do you mean?

192
00:13:11,640 --> 00:13:13,800
It's a shame she came back too late.

193
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:16,720
Otherwise, I would've wanted her
as my daughter-in-law.

194
00:13:16,720 --> 00:13:18,240
Don't be ridiculous!

195
00:13:18,240 --> 00:13:20,880
What's wrong with that? I was only thinking.

196
00:13:20,880 --> 00:13:22,240
Then keep it as a thought.

197
00:13:23,040 --> 00:13:25,000
Try not to commit sins, okay?

198
00:13:25,720 --> 00:13:27,000
What are you talking about?

199
00:13:27,160 --> 00:13:29,040
Trying to break up someone's marriage is wrong.

200
00:13:29,120 --> 00:13:30,280
I'm warning you.

201
00:13:31,760 --> 00:13:34,120
Hmph! Such a know-it-all. But I don't care.

202
00:13:34,880 --> 00:13:36,360
I should call Runch.

203
00:13:56,320 --> 00:13:59,480
MOM

204
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:05,360
Just answer it already,
or she'll keep calling nonstop.

205
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:10,080
Yes, Mom?

206
00:14:10,160 --> 00:14:12,760
Runch, let's have lunch together today.

207
00:14:13,720 --> 00:14:15,360
I can't today, Mom.

208
00:14:15,960 --> 00:14:18,160
What do you mean you can't?

209
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:19,720
You're busy all day?

210
00:14:20,680 --> 00:14:23,720
Can't you spare a few hours for me?

211
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:26,520
I really can't today, Mom.

212
00:14:27,360 --> 00:14:29,400
Maylin's coming too.

213
00:14:30,120 --> 00:14:31,680
She wanted to see you.

214
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:36,640
Sorry, Mom. I can't make it.

215
00:14:37,160 --> 00:14:41,400
I'm on my way
to Neen's grandparents' country house.

216
00:14:42,160 --> 00:14:44,040
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

217
00:14:44,040 --> 00:14:45,920
I already invited Maylin.

218
00:14:46,120 --> 00:14:48,480
She's going to be disappointed if you don't come.

219
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:53,440
Are you far already?

220
00:14:53,480 --> 00:14:55,080
Can't you come back first?

221
00:14:56,040 --> 00:14:57,800
You can head there after lunch.

222
00:14:57,800 --> 00:15:00,320
Ugh, that's impossible, Mother.

223
00:15:00,320 --> 00:15:02,560
We're already more than halfway there.

224
00:15:02,560 --> 00:15:04,400
Turning back now would just waste time.

225
00:15:04,560 --> 00:15:06,280
You put me on speaker, Runch?

226
00:15:06,640 --> 00:15:07,600
Yeah, Mom.

227
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:09,560
I'm driving.

228
00:15:10,240 --> 00:15:12,160
We really can't make it, Mother.

229
00:15:12,160 --> 00:15:14,720
Just tell your precious Maylin.

230
00:15:14,720 --> 00:15:18,680
Buy her a lollipop or something to cheer up, okay?

231
00:15:18,680 --> 00:15:21,480
I'm hanging up now.
Runch needs to focus on driving.

232
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:31,000
That little brat… She actually hung up on me?

233
00:15:45,280 --> 00:15:46,280
Neen,

234
00:15:46,640 --> 00:15:48,520
why are you mad at me?

235
00:15:48,840 --> 00:15:49,800
I'm not mad.

236
00:15:50,360 --> 00:15:53,320
Come on. You're clearly upset.

237
00:15:53,800 --> 00:15:55,760
I can explain about Maylin.

238
00:15:58,480 --> 00:16:00,600
So you do know why I'm upset. Then why ask?

239
00:16:01,960 --> 00:16:03,360
I can tell…

240
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:05,880
-You're jealous.
-I'm not jealous.

241
00:16:07,280 --> 00:16:09,560
Why would I be? We're getting divorced anyway.

242
00:16:10,080 --> 00:16:12,840
She's just my mom's best friend's daughter.

243
00:16:13,240 --> 00:16:15,040
We used to play together as kids.

244
00:16:15,440 --> 00:16:17,640
That's all.

245
00:16:19,320 --> 00:16:22,040
Your mom clearly doesn't see it that way.

246
00:16:22,240 --> 00:16:23,960
She practically set the two of you up.

247
00:16:26,760 --> 00:16:27,960
Neen…

248
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:35,400
Don't be mad at me, okay?

249
00:16:38,080 --> 00:16:40,560
If your grandparents see this,

250
00:16:40,720 --> 00:16:42,800
they'll notice right away.

251
00:16:43,800 --> 00:16:45,920
They'll worry.

252
00:16:47,360 --> 00:16:49,800
They want to see us happy, remember?

253
00:16:52,120 --> 00:16:53,800
Hold my hand when we go in, okay?

254
00:17:10,319 --> 00:17:11,839
Grandpa? Grandma?

255
00:17:11,839 --> 00:17:15,680
Oh my, look who came all the way out here!

256
00:17:15,680 --> 00:17:18,240
I missed you so much!

257
00:17:19,960 --> 00:17:21,920
You're always such a sweetheart.

258
00:17:22,240 --> 00:17:23,520
I missed you too.

259
00:17:23,640 --> 00:17:24,920
I missed you too.

260
00:17:24,920 --> 00:17:26,240
Hey, let me hug her too!

261
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:29,080
Goodness, you're so impatient.

262
00:17:33,800 --> 00:17:35,440
You've gotten so skinny.

263
00:17:35,840 --> 00:17:37,600
Have you been eating properly?

264
00:17:38,040 --> 00:17:40,640
Or is Runch making you stay thin like a model?

265
00:17:41,760 --> 00:17:46,640
Hey, I didn't ask her to do that.

266
00:17:47,720 --> 00:17:49,160
I eat just fine.

267
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:51,800
And I'm perfectly healthy, so don't worry.

268
00:17:53,640 --> 00:17:54,600
Runch,

269
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:57,000
it has been a while, hasn't it?

270
00:17:57,560 --> 00:17:59,560
You've gotten even prettier.

271
00:17:59,960 --> 00:18:00,880
Thank you.

272
00:18:02,680 --> 00:18:03,760
What about me?

273
00:18:06,240 --> 00:18:09,640
You know you'll always be the prettiest to me.

274
00:18:12,120 --> 00:18:15,600
I missed you both so much. Are you two doing well?

275
00:18:15,680 --> 00:18:17,680
-We're doing well.
-Yeah, we're good.

276
00:18:27,800 --> 00:18:29,880
Grandma asked what we want for lunch.

277
00:18:30,720 --> 00:18:32,120
I'm good with anything.

278
00:18:32,880 --> 00:18:33,840
Okay, I'll let her know.

279
00:18:36,320 --> 00:18:38,800
Want to go for a walk? The weather's nice.

280
00:18:42,480 --> 00:18:43,440
Sure.

281
00:18:43,960 --> 00:18:45,880
It has been a while since we did that.

282
00:18:46,920 --> 00:18:50,160
We used to go on walks together all the time.

283
00:18:52,680 --> 00:18:53,560
Okay.

284
00:18:54,640 --> 00:18:57,520
Then let's do it after lunch.

285
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:09,160
Say what you want,

286
00:19:09,160 --> 00:19:13,280
but you just want an excuse to spend time with me.

287
00:19:13,880 --> 00:19:15,040
I know you too well.

288
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:28,560
We'll eat first, then go for a walk.

289
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:30,800
Come on.

290
00:19:38,880 --> 00:19:41,400
Do you ever want to live like my grandparents?

291
00:19:42,760 --> 00:19:45,640
You wouldn't be happy living out here.

292
00:19:47,720 --> 00:19:49,000
I'm asking about you.

293
00:19:49,400 --> 00:19:50,720
Would you want this kind of life?

294
00:19:51,840 --> 00:19:53,360
I like being with you.

295
00:19:57,080 --> 00:19:58,080
Nice try.

296
00:20:17,240 --> 00:20:18,520
For you, milady.

297
00:20:21,160 --> 00:20:24,680
Wow. Not even store-bought. You're so cheap.

298
00:20:27,560 --> 00:20:30,920
Sorry, I'm not Ms. Peeracha Pacharathakul,

299
00:20:31,240 --> 00:20:36,800
buying a giant bouquet for Employee of the Year.

300
00:20:37,920 --> 00:20:39,560
You liked it though, didn't you?

301
00:20:42,120 --> 00:20:43,880
Back then…

302
00:20:44,840 --> 00:20:46,440
I felt a lot of things.

303
00:21:01,960 --> 00:21:05,160
Congratulations on Employee of the Year.
And your promotion too!

304
00:21:09,560 --> 00:21:10,600
Thank you.

305
00:21:11,280 --> 00:21:12,760
But how did you know?

306
00:21:13,800 --> 00:21:17,600
Well… my last name is Pacharathakul.

307
00:21:19,160 --> 00:21:20,600
Pacharathakul?

308
00:21:21,560 --> 00:21:23,680
You have Mr. Aphichet's last name?

309
00:21:24,120 --> 00:21:25,160
That's my boss…

310
00:21:26,920 --> 00:21:27,840
That's right.

311
00:21:29,280 --> 00:21:31,560
Mr. Aphichet is my uncle.

312
00:21:36,080 --> 00:21:37,480
Is it a nice last name?

313
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:39,320
Want to use it someday?

314
00:21:46,280 --> 00:21:48,840
Wait. This award and promotion…

315
00:21:50,080 --> 00:21:52,280
You didn't pull strings for me, did you?

316
00:21:53,040 --> 00:21:55,920
We're not even dating yet. Why would I?

317
00:21:56,360 --> 00:21:59,760
And if we were dating? Would you?

318
00:22:00,840 --> 00:22:01,680
No.

319
00:22:03,360 --> 00:22:05,760
If you don't believe me… try dating me and see.

320
00:22:07,120 --> 00:22:08,080
What did you just say?

321
00:22:11,200 --> 00:22:12,520
I'm asking you out.

322
00:22:12,520 --> 00:22:13,320
Huh?!

323
00:22:15,680 --> 00:22:16,720
Date me.

324
00:22:18,680 --> 00:22:20,280
Hold on. Wait, what?!

325
00:22:23,680 --> 00:22:24,960
Are you nervous?

326
00:22:25,600 --> 00:22:27,240
Aren't you?

327
00:22:27,680 --> 00:22:29,760
We've been getting along pretty well.

328
00:22:30,200 --> 00:22:32,600
Well… yeah, that's true.

329
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:37,840
Then we should date.

330
00:22:41,680 --> 00:22:42,680
Fine.

331
00:22:42,880 --> 00:22:44,600
I'll give you some time to think about it.

332
00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:51,640
I've already decided.

333
00:22:53,400 --> 00:22:54,280
Yes.

334
00:22:59,040 --> 00:23:00,240
Wait… Hold on!

335
00:23:00,400 --> 00:23:01,320
Stop.

336
00:23:01,880 --> 00:23:04,320
Someone might see us.

337
00:23:06,880 --> 00:23:07,720
Fine.

338
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:10,760
But now you owe me a kiss.

339
00:23:11,280 --> 00:23:13,760
Next time… I'm not holding back.

340
00:23:14,680 --> 00:23:18,720
♪ And you'll love so deeply ♪

341
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:22,560
♪ Can you feel my love? ♪

342
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:28,080
♪ Please know that I love you ♪

343
00:23:31,160 --> 00:23:32,400
You remember that?

344
00:23:33,920 --> 00:23:35,920
I never forget…

345
00:23:37,160 --> 00:23:38,480
anything about you.

346
00:23:46,160 --> 00:23:47,600
Come on, let's go inside.

347
00:23:48,280 --> 00:23:50,840
My grandparents are probably waiting for us.

348
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:54,880
Are you shy?

349
00:23:56,800 --> 00:23:58,400
What? Why would I be shy?

350
00:23:58,400 --> 00:23:59,440
You're blushing.

351
00:23:59,640 --> 00:24:01,520
It's hot outside, okay?

352
00:24:03,360 --> 00:24:04,800
Stay here if you want.

353
00:24:08,880 --> 00:24:12,320
What's the secret to staying together for so long?

354
00:24:13,440 --> 00:24:16,240
There's no secret formula.

355
00:24:16,720 --> 00:24:20,800
Every couple has their own style.

356
00:24:21,800 --> 00:24:24,640
You just have to be patient with one another.

357
00:24:25,720 --> 00:24:28,240
Sounds simple, right?

358
00:24:28,800 --> 00:24:32,040
But for some people, that's hard.

359
00:24:32,640 --> 00:24:33,840
I agree.

360
00:24:34,280 --> 00:24:36,480
Relationships

361
00:24:36,720 --> 00:24:39,400
are built on lots of little things.

362
00:24:39,480 --> 00:24:42,800
Your grandma and I went through a lot

363
00:24:43,640 --> 00:24:46,240
before we got here.

364
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:48,240
We fought.

365
00:24:50,080 --> 00:24:51,640
We disagreed.

366
00:24:52,040 --> 00:24:53,280
We cried together

367
00:24:53,840 --> 00:24:56,440
more times than I can count.

368
00:24:58,760 --> 00:25:02,360
Your wedding last year

369
00:25:02,960 --> 00:25:04,840
was only the beginning.

370
00:25:05,320 --> 00:25:06,720
Like I said,

371
00:25:07,880 --> 00:25:09,960
patience matters.

372
00:25:10,480 --> 00:25:13,920
If you're honest and patient with each other,

373
00:25:14,440 --> 00:25:17,520
a lot of problems can be worked through.

374
00:25:18,080 --> 00:25:21,640
Patience gives you time to think

375
00:25:22,080 --> 00:25:24,000
before you speak

376
00:25:24,400 --> 00:25:25,880
or act,

377
00:25:26,280 --> 00:25:28,360
instead of letting emotions

378
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:30,680
make things worse.

379
00:25:31,560 --> 00:25:33,520
So between the two of you…

380
00:25:34,400 --> 00:25:35,760
who's more patient?

381
00:25:37,960 --> 00:25:40,000
Probably him.

382
00:25:40,200 --> 00:25:41,680
You see,

383
00:25:41,880 --> 00:25:44,480
I had quite a temper when I was younger.

384
00:25:47,880 --> 00:25:51,320
Then what made you become more patient?

385
00:25:51,360 --> 00:25:52,320
Hmm…

386
00:25:52,760 --> 00:25:56,000
probably his handsome face.

387
00:25:56,360 --> 00:25:57,800
Same here.

388
00:25:58,080 --> 00:26:00,200
No wonder we're family.

389
00:26:01,200 --> 00:26:04,160
Every time I look at Runch's pretty face,

390
00:26:04,400 --> 00:26:06,400
I go soft immediately.

391
00:26:07,520 --> 00:26:10,080
Seeing the two of you like this
makes me really happy.

392
00:26:10,640 --> 00:26:12,520
I hope you stay in love

393
00:26:12,520 --> 00:26:14,960
and grow old together.

394
00:26:28,320 --> 00:26:30,520
Help me move these roses into the pots.

395
00:26:30,560 --> 00:26:31,680
Can you do it?

396
00:26:31,680 --> 00:26:32,560
Of course.

397
00:26:33,320 --> 00:26:38,120
I used to grow plants all the time
before I started working.

398
00:26:39,080 --> 00:26:40,000
Good.

399
00:26:40,240 --> 00:26:41,800
Then I'll leave this to you two.

400
00:26:42,240 --> 00:26:43,600
-Got it.
-Okay.

401
00:26:56,360 --> 00:26:58,960
I didn't know you were into plants.

402
00:27:00,200 --> 00:27:01,840
Back in university,

403
00:27:02,080 --> 00:27:06,160
I loved going to plant markets
and bringing plants home.

404
00:27:06,200 --> 00:27:08,400
But once work got busy, I stopped.

405
00:27:23,400 --> 00:27:27,920
You know white roses are my favorite, right?

406
00:27:28,720 --> 00:27:29,680
Of course.

407
00:27:31,440 --> 00:27:33,240
Do you remember why?

408
00:27:35,480 --> 00:27:36,560
I don't know.

409
00:27:37,160 --> 00:27:38,320
Because they're pretty?

410
00:27:39,440 --> 00:27:43,520
They represent pure love,

411
00:27:43,880 --> 00:27:45,080
graceful love,

412
00:27:46,040 --> 00:27:48,840
eternal love, and new beginnings.

413
00:27:51,680 --> 00:27:53,120
That's so cheesy.

414
00:27:54,560 --> 00:27:55,640
Eternal love?

415
00:27:56,560 --> 00:27:57,960
There's no such thing.

416
00:28:07,160 --> 00:28:08,480
What are you laughing at?

417
00:28:09,520 --> 00:28:11,120
Nothing.

418
00:28:11,640 --> 00:28:12,520
Nothing at all.

419
00:28:14,120 --> 00:28:15,000
What?

420
00:28:20,720 --> 00:28:22,520
Is there something on my face?

421
00:28:24,160 --> 00:28:25,600
I'll wipe it off for you.

422
00:28:28,880 --> 00:28:31,040
You're so pretty.

423
00:28:32,000 --> 00:28:34,080
Even with dirt on your face.

424
00:28:36,520 --> 00:28:37,520
All good.

425
00:28:39,960 --> 00:28:41,000
Get all of it off.

426
00:28:41,120 --> 00:28:42,160
Did you?

427
00:28:42,640 --> 00:28:45,560
I'll clean the rest later. Just…

428
00:28:45,800 --> 00:28:46,800
It's fine now.

429
00:28:54,400 --> 00:28:57,520
♪ In the moments when we look at each other ♪

430
00:28:57,880 --> 00:29:00,800
♪ Even if I don't say it out loud ♪

431
00:29:00,800 --> 00:29:04,440
♪ Deep inside, I only care about you ♪

432
00:29:04,440 --> 00:29:07,920
♪ Love is so magical ♪

433
00:29:09,160 --> 00:29:12,920
♪ Even though sometimes I don't treat you right ♪

434
00:29:12,960 --> 00:29:15,720
♪ And there aren't many sweet words ♪

435
00:29:15,720 --> 00:29:18,040
♪ But I want you to know that ♪

436
00:29:18,040 --> 00:29:22,680
♪ My life partner will always be you ♪

437
00:29:23,720 --> 00:29:25,160
Grandpa! Grandma!

438
00:29:26,720 --> 00:29:28,920
We finished planting the roses.

439
00:29:28,920 --> 00:29:31,240
Anything else you want us to help with?

440
00:29:42,240 --> 00:29:43,560
This thing is huge.

441
00:29:44,320 --> 00:29:45,520
How are we supposed to wash it?

442
00:29:48,320 --> 00:29:49,440
I know a way.

443
00:30:00,120 --> 00:30:02,320
I didn't know you could wash it like this.

444
00:30:02,360 --> 00:30:03,480
It's actually kind of fun.

445
00:30:21,880 --> 00:30:23,040
You can let go now.

446
00:30:23,920 --> 00:30:26,280
If I let go, you'll fall.

447
00:30:28,360 --> 00:30:30,520
Let's stay like this. It feels nice.

448
00:30:33,440 --> 00:30:34,240
Okay.

449
00:30:48,360 --> 00:30:49,240
Oh!

450
00:30:49,480 --> 00:30:51,920
Hurry, take a picture!

451
00:30:56,360 --> 00:30:58,200
Quick, send it.

452
00:30:58,960 --> 00:30:59,960
HOW'S IT GOING, MOM?

453
00:31:00,320 --> 00:31:01,480
Perfect.

454
00:31:02,240 --> 00:31:03,760
Did you get the photo, Kae?

455
00:31:03,760 --> 00:31:05,040
I did, Mom.

456
00:31:05,080 --> 00:31:07,240
I really hope your plan works.

457
00:31:07,840 --> 00:31:09,280
It has to work.

458
00:31:09,720 --> 00:31:12,440
I'll make sure those two

459
00:31:12,440 --> 00:31:15,000
change their minds about the divorce.

460
00:31:15,360 --> 00:31:19,160
I'm sure they have to feel something at least.

461
00:31:20,160 --> 00:31:21,440
We're really counting on you, Mother.

462
00:31:21,640 --> 00:31:25,600
Honestly, we also don't want them to divorce.

463
00:31:26,440 --> 00:31:29,560
It breaks my heart every time I think about it.

464
00:31:29,560 --> 00:31:32,800
I could understand if they were divorcing
because of disagreement,

465
00:31:32,800 --> 00:31:35,840
but divorcing because of someone else…
I just can't accept that.

466
00:31:36,080 --> 00:31:38,040
We've tried everything we can.

467
00:31:38,040 --> 00:31:41,440
When they told us, all we could do was respect it.

468
00:31:41,880 --> 00:31:43,720
But we don't want that to happen.

469
00:31:44,440 --> 00:31:46,200
Looking at the photo,

470
00:31:46,400 --> 00:31:48,680
if they stay there another two weeks,

471
00:31:48,680 --> 00:31:51,320
they might actually reconcile.

472
00:31:54,560 --> 00:31:55,680
Mm.

473
00:31:56,440 --> 00:31:57,840
Leave it to us.

474
00:31:58,920 --> 00:32:00,400
Just wait and see.

475
00:32:04,880 --> 00:32:08,280
♪ Can you hear me saying I love you? ♪

476
00:32:08,280 --> 00:32:10,200
♪ Use the feeling you know ♪

477
00:32:10,200 --> 00:32:14,400
♪ And you'll love so deeply ♪

478
00:32:14,400 --> 00:32:18,240
♪ Can you feel my love? ♪

479
00:32:18,400 --> 00:32:21,160
♪ Please know that I love you ♪

480
00:32:22,720 --> 00:32:25,640
I'm sorry Runch couldn't make it today.

481
00:32:25,640 --> 00:32:27,880
She's busy with work.

482
00:32:29,920 --> 00:32:32,840
It's okay, Auntie. I understand.

483
00:32:33,520 --> 00:32:35,200
That's typical of an attorney.

484
00:32:35,640 --> 00:32:36,680
You barely get any time to rest.

485
00:32:38,080 --> 00:32:41,600
You're so understanding, Maylin.
That's very sweet of you.

486
00:32:42,840 --> 00:32:45,440
I've admired Runch ever since we were kids.

487
00:32:45,920 --> 00:32:48,720
She always looked so cool,
no matter what she was doing.

488
00:32:48,920 --> 00:32:52,360
I actually studied law because of her too.

489
00:32:53,280 --> 00:32:56,880
She told me
she wanted to become an attorney someday…

490
00:32:57,240 --> 00:32:58,720
and she really did it.

491
00:32:59,080 --> 00:33:00,040
Mm.

492
00:33:00,080 --> 00:33:02,360
So I wanted to follow in her footsteps.

493
00:33:03,280 --> 00:33:05,080
Sounds like you really admire her.

494
00:33:06,840 --> 00:33:08,240
I do.

495
00:33:11,720 --> 00:33:12,760
Maylin…

496
00:33:13,600 --> 00:33:15,280
can I ask you something honestly?

497
00:33:16,080 --> 00:33:16,920
Of course.

498
00:33:17,120 --> 00:33:18,800
You like Runch, don't you?

499
00:33:22,040 --> 00:33:23,160
Auntie…

500
00:33:26,600 --> 00:33:28,120
You can tell me.

501
00:33:28,120 --> 00:33:31,320
These days, women liking women
isn't unusual anymore.

502
00:33:31,360 --> 00:33:32,560
I understand.

503
00:33:37,520 --> 00:33:38,480
I do.

504
00:33:39,480 --> 00:33:41,000
I've liked Runch…

505
00:33:42,080 --> 00:33:43,560
for a long time.

506
00:33:49,000 --> 00:33:50,120
Here, eat more, dear.

507
00:33:50,440 --> 00:33:51,440
Thank you.

508
00:34:01,200 --> 00:34:03,240
Runch, come here for a second.

509
00:34:03,520 --> 00:34:05,080
Sure. What's wrong?

510
00:34:05,560 --> 00:34:06,360
Come here.

511
00:34:08,920 --> 00:34:10,480
Neen's in the shower, right?

512
00:34:10,880 --> 00:34:12,400
Yes, she just went in.

513
00:34:12,600 --> 00:34:13,560
Why?

514
00:34:13,560 --> 00:34:15,800
We have something important to talk to you about.

515
00:34:16,239 --> 00:34:17,440
Something important?

516
00:34:18,480 --> 00:34:21,760
Neen's birthday is coming up in a few days.

517
00:34:22,440 --> 00:34:24,360
I know.

518
00:34:25,000 --> 00:34:28,840
We want to surprise her early

519
00:34:29,159 --> 00:34:30,679
while she's here.

520
00:34:31,719 --> 00:34:35,400
So she can take her mind off things

521
00:34:35,400 --> 00:34:38,000
and really relax for once.

522
00:34:38,920 --> 00:34:40,520
It has been such a long time

523
00:34:40,520 --> 00:34:45,000
since we've heard her laugh like before.

524
00:34:46,880 --> 00:34:49,239
Please help us, Runch.

525
00:34:50,480 --> 00:34:54,120
You're the person who knows her best.

526
00:34:57,320 --> 00:34:59,200
Of course.

527
00:34:59,760 --> 00:35:01,840
I'll handle everything.

528
00:35:02,040 --> 00:35:03,120
Mm.

529
00:35:03,520 --> 00:35:05,760
Neen is very lucky

530
00:35:05,960 --> 00:35:08,720
to have someone who loves her this much.

531
00:35:11,480 --> 00:35:13,120
Let's make a plan.

532
00:35:13,520 --> 00:35:15,720
And don't let her find out.

533
00:35:16,280 --> 00:35:17,080
Got it.

534
00:35:24,200 --> 00:35:25,200
This is good.

535
00:35:25,200 --> 00:35:26,320
Oh, thanks.

536
00:35:26,880 --> 00:35:27,800
Try this too.

537
00:35:30,480 --> 00:35:31,440
Neen,

538
00:35:31,560 --> 00:35:34,880
your grandmother and I
need to stop by the temple for a bit.

539
00:35:35,480 --> 00:35:38,560
Can you drive us there?

540
00:35:39,960 --> 00:35:42,360
Of course. I'll take you.

541
00:35:43,400 --> 00:35:46,440
Runch, can you stay
and look after the house while we're gone?

542
00:35:47,000 --> 00:35:48,600
You don't need to do much.

543
00:35:48,640 --> 00:35:50,720
Just clean up the dishes for us, okay?

544
00:35:51,240 --> 00:35:52,480
Sure.

545
00:35:52,760 --> 00:35:54,680
I'll take care of everything.

546
00:35:55,440 --> 00:35:58,520
Perfect. Then we'll head out after this.

547
00:35:58,520 --> 00:35:59,400
Sounds good.

548
00:35:59,400 --> 00:36:00,760
Now eat up, okay?

549
00:36:01,000 --> 00:36:02,400
Eat a lot.

550
00:37:01,440 --> 00:37:02,440
Runch?

551
00:37:06,120 --> 00:37:07,280
Runch?

552
00:37:12,120 --> 00:37:13,560
Where are you?

553
00:37:39,760 --> 00:37:40,760
Runch?

554
00:37:43,120 --> 00:37:43,960
Runch?

555
00:37:49,600 --> 00:37:50,600
Runch?

556
00:38:42,240 --> 00:38:43,080
Runch…

557
00:38:52,160 --> 00:38:53,520
What's all this?

558
00:38:55,040 --> 00:38:59,160
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

559
00:38:59,440 --> 00:39:01,040
Happy early birthday.

560
00:39:02,960 --> 00:39:04,880
Make a wish first then blow out the candles.

561
00:39:35,040 --> 00:39:38,720
Your grandparents won't be back tonight.

562
00:39:39,920 --> 00:39:42,240
They're staying over at a friend's house.

563
00:39:43,280 --> 00:39:44,160
Mm.

564
00:39:44,480 --> 00:39:46,800
They told me too.

565
00:39:48,120 --> 00:39:50,440
Which means…

566
00:39:51,520 --> 00:39:55,120
it's just the two of us tonight.

567
00:39:56,160 --> 00:39:57,000
Mm.

568
00:39:58,920 --> 00:40:00,120
So…

569
00:40:01,600 --> 00:40:03,200
what should we do then?

570
00:40:18,520 --> 00:40:19,760
It's beautiful out here.

571
00:40:20,960 --> 00:40:23,600
I've never really looked at the stars here.

572
00:40:25,680 --> 00:40:26,720
I know.

573
00:40:27,720 --> 00:40:30,600
That's why I brought you here.

574
00:40:37,040 --> 00:40:41,400
I used to love stargazing when I was little.

575
00:40:42,680 --> 00:40:45,600
But these days, I barely even look up anymore.

576
00:40:50,680 --> 00:40:51,560
Oh?

577
00:40:52,200 --> 00:40:53,120
Runch…

578
00:40:54,080 --> 00:40:55,560
did you see a shooting star?

579
00:40:59,440 --> 00:41:00,920
It's really--

580
00:41:01,080 --> 00:41:04,640
♪ In the moments when we look at each other ♪

581
00:41:04,720 --> 00:41:07,680
♪ Even if I don't say it out loud ♪

582
00:41:07,680 --> 00:41:11,320
♪ Deep inside, I only worry about you ♪

583
00:41:11,360 --> 00:41:14,400
♪ Love is so magical ♪

584
00:41:16,040 --> 00:41:19,800
♪ Even though sometimes I don't treat you right ♪

585
00:41:19,800 --> 00:41:22,560
♪ And there aren't many sweet words ♪

586
00:41:22,560 --> 00:41:25,000
♪ But I want you to know that ♪

587
00:41:25,040 --> 00:41:29,480
♪ My life partner will always be you ♪

588
00:41:29,800 --> 00:41:33,400
♪ I'm weak for your lips ♪

589
00:41:33,400 --> 00:41:37,320
♪ And the kiss upon my forehead ♪

590
00:41:37,320 --> 00:41:43,520
♪ Every action conveys these words, you know? ♪

591
00:41:44,200 --> 00:41:47,920
♪ Can you hear me saying I love you? ♪

592
00:41:47,920 --> 00:41:51,640
♪ My love is in these soft whispers ♪

593
00:41:51,680 --> 00:41:54,000
♪ You have to feel it with your heart ♪

594
00:41:54,000 --> 00:41:59,240
♪ Our touches will make you understand ♪

595
00:41:59,240 --> 00:42:02,600
♪ Can you hear me saying I love you? ♪

596
00:42:02,600 --> 00:42:04,440
♪ Use the feeling you know ♪

597
00:42:04,440 --> 00:42:08,760
♪ And you'll love so deeply ♪

598
00:42:08,760 --> 00:42:12,800
♪ Can you feel my love? ♪

599
00:42:12,800 --> 00:42:16,040
♪ Please know that I love you ♪

600
00:42:18,880 --> 00:42:19,840
THREE YEARS AGO

601
00:42:19,840 --> 00:42:21,720
The sunset's beautiful.

602
00:42:22,600 --> 00:42:25,440
Still not as beautiful as you.

603
00:42:28,200 --> 00:42:29,800
Your lips are sweet.

604
00:42:31,080 --> 00:42:32,480
Oh? Have you tasted them before?

605
00:42:32,480 --> 00:42:34,320
How would you know?

606
00:42:34,880 --> 00:42:35,880
Not yet.

607
00:42:38,320 --> 00:42:39,680
But I kind of want to now.

608
00:42:40,360 --> 00:42:42,280
I want to find out if they're really sweet.

609
00:42:45,040 --> 00:42:47,240
Today's officially our first day together.

610
00:42:48,680 --> 00:42:50,960
So… may I kiss you?

611
00:42:51,320 --> 00:42:55,240
♪ I'm weak for your lips ♪

612
00:42:55,240 --> 00:42:59,280
♪ And the kiss upon my forehead ♪

613
00:42:59,280 --> 00:43:05,640
♪ Every action conveys these words, you know? ♪

614
00:43:05,960 --> 00:43:09,760
♪ Can you hear me saying I love you? ♪

615
00:43:09,760 --> 00:43:13,520
♪ My love is in these soft whispers ♪

616
00:43:13,520 --> 00:43:15,920
♪ You have to feel it with your heart ♪

617
00:43:15,920 --> 00:43:21,000
♪ Our touches will make you understand ♪

618
00:43:21,000 --> 00:43:24,520
♪ Can you hear me saying I love you? ♪

619
00:43:24,520 --> 00:43:26,200
♪ Use the feeling you know ♪

620
00:43:26,200 --> 00:43:30,640
♪ And you'll love so deeply ♪

621
00:43:30,640 --> 00:43:34,560
♪ Can you feel my love? ♪

622
00:43:34,560 --> 00:43:37,200
♪ Please know that I love you ♪

623
00:43:37,200 --> 00:43:40,080
Runch and that new employee

624
00:43:40,080 --> 00:43:43,880
have been getting a little too close lately.

625
00:43:43,960 --> 00:43:45,800
You made me feel like

626
00:43:45,800 --> 00:43:48,360
there's a whole side of you I don't even know.

627
00:43:48,440 --> 00:43:49,560
You crazy minx!

628
00:43:49,560 --> 00:43:51,000
You've ruined everything!

629
00:43:51,000 --> 00:43:52,320
You're the one who did that.

630
00:43:52,320 --> 00:43:54,560
What now? Are you trying to find Runch a mistress?

631
00:43:55,880 --> 00:43:59,480
I did all of this to protect you.

632
00:43:59,640 --> 00:44:02,800
I won't let anyone hurt my wife's feelings.

633
00:44:03,680 --> 00:44:04,920
No matter who it is.

634
00:44:05,120 --> 00:44:06,520
Not even you, Mom.

635
00:44:09,080 --> 00:44:11,880
♪ Living with pain and love ♪

636
00:44:11,880 --> 00:44:14,680
♪ Living while waiting and losing hope ♪

637
00:44:14,680 --> 00:44:17,120
♪ A voice inside my heart says enough ♪

638
00:44:17,160 --> 00:44:20,240
♪ But another voice asks me to endure ♪

639
00:44:20,240 --> 00:44:22,960
♪ I stay because I love you, you know? ♪

640
00:44:22,960 --> 00:44:28,800
♪ I still believe in the love between us ♪

641
00:44:29,280 --> 00:44:33,840
